The paper deals with the design and implementation of a purely functional data structure for the linearisation case of dynamic trees problem. This falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses different implementations and performance measurements, which could fall under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the use of finger trees, a popular data structure in functional programming, could also make this paper relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) as it is often used in the implementation of neural networks.
